    teachingPoint: 'Stereotype threat: situational activation of identity-based negative stereotypes impairs performance in the threatened domain. Key features: (1) affects high-performing group members most (more invested in domain), (2) removed by non-evaluative framing, (3) cognitive mechanism — threat consumes working memory resources. Interventions: self-affirmation, growth mindset framing, non-diagnostic framing, belonging messages. Applies to multiple groups: women in math, elderly on memory tests, white athletes in basketball, etc.',
