    correctAnswer: 'C',
    explanation: 'Choice C is correct. Mirror-tracing improvement = procedural learning — a form of implicit memory (motor skill acquisition). Procedural memory does NOT require the hippocampus; it depends on the striatum and cerebellum. This mirrors classic cases (e.g., H.M.) of bilateral hippocampal damage. "Cannot recall having done the task" = impaired episodic memory (memory for specific past events — autobiographical, explicit). "Does not recognize her neurologist" = failure to form new declarative memories (specifically new episodic memories for faces and events encountered after the damage — anterograde amnesia). Hippocampal damage impairs formation of new declarative (explicit) memories while leaving implicit memory systems (procedural, priming) intact.',
